{
  "stem": "1858.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it was, again, another means of instilling fear in us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But as I was saying before, that how we were being deceived all the time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, they would come suddenly at night, force your front door open, and by the time you were awakened, by the time you began to realize what's happening, several members of your home were taken away.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Or from time to time, they would send a notification that you are to report to the Umschlagplatz, for young people.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But it was during one of those raids, those nightly raids, that they surrounded our street and it was lit up and they forced their way into our home that one of my sisters was taken away.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she, my sister Mania, she was the first one to be sent to a labor camp, deep into Germany.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "At first we used to get postcards from her, telling us that she's working, that everything is orderly.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We knew and realized that this is what she is forced to say, that she cannot really open up and say what she feels.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was painful because our family was growing smaller all the time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My sister who lived in Kielce, we lost contact with her completely.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And my brother was there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Then here my sister was taken away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So our family was growing smaller all the time, and the sadness was setting in as time went on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I remember in '41 and '42, there were no more books to be gotten for a Jewish child because the libraries were closed to us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "You could not-- in Poland, in order to be a member of a library, you had to be a member and pay dues.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
